The President of the Abuja Original Inhabitants Youth Empowerment Organisation (AOIYEO), Commandant Isaac David, has congratulated Muslim faithful in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on the occasion of the eid-fitr celebration. In a statement, AOIYEO President, urged all the faithful to abide by the lessons learnt during the holy month of Ramadan. He said the doctrine of Islamic faith was premised on sacrifice as well as peace and pleaded with the residents to continue to live harmoniously with their neighbours. He also pleaded with the residents to continue to pray for the FCT administration and the country at large over the present security challenges.